  foaf:homepage <https://www.avl.nl/multitargetFIT>;
  dcterms:description "The mulitarget FIT study is a prospective study that is running within the Dutch National CRC screening program. The aim of this study is to compare the performance of a new stool test (mtFIT) with the currently used FIT. In this study we collect the lab data (results mtFIT and FIT) as well as the clinical data associated; age and sex of participants, colonoscopy findings (when one or both tests are positive), pathology data (when a lesion is detected during colonoscopy).";
  dcat:keyword "biomarkers", "early detection of cancer", "routine diagnostic tests",
